args:
The Holy City of Grams lies in ruins. Though
Satan has been sent hence, the miasma has yet
to subside and fiends run rampantâ€”making any
effort at reconstruction impossible. The prince
and his allies continue to struggle amidst this
dark atmosphere that pervades through the city.
They just keep comin'! Hurry up and die\nalready, ya piece'a crap fiends!
I got things pretty much mopped up.
Which means we have dealt with the last\nof the fiends in this area.
Ranzal! Elly! There's trouble, more fiends!
The hell's goin' on here? There's no end\nto 'em!
We succeeded in sealing Satan away,\nyet the miasma shows no signs of abating.\nWhat in the name of the Goddess IS this?
Our fierce battle at the Sacred Tree saw us\npromising to fight at Nedrick's side.
After that, we got news that the Holy City\nof Grams was under attack from Satan.
We rushed to the city and managed to seal\nthe demon away with the help of the apostles,\nthe angels, and Auspex Origa.
With that done, I thought Grams would join\nwith their former enemy of Alberia and move\nforward toward reconstruction. And yet...
Leave this to us. All of you hurry up and\nget out of here!
I'll not permit you to interfere with the\nreconstruction any longer, fiend!
I don't see any more fiends.\nMaybe we finally did it this time?
I fear that is unlikely. While this batch\nof fiends may have been dispatched,\nthe miasma shows no signs of clearing.
I wager we shall be dealing with more\nmiasma-spawned fiends erelong.
Which means we need a new plan if we\never wanna get this city rebuilt.
Agreed. We cannot even begin clearing\nrubble when we lack the faintest notion\nof where or when fiends may appear.
But fixin' buildings and homes don't mean\nsquat if the folks what live here ain't on\nboard with the plan.
Morale in this joint is lower than a snake\nin a wheel rut, and folks are startin' to\nthink they'll never rebuild the place.
Can you blame 'em? The moment they\nfinally fix something, fiends show up\nand smash it to bits all over again!
It makes my tummy hurt just thinking\nabout it. Blech.
We must take action before the denizens\nof Grams lose all hope.
This miasma stuff is something Satan\nleft behind, right?
But since we already sealed him away,\nhow the heck do we get rid of it?

For now, we need more bodies. If we keep
tryin' to handle this by ourselves, we're
gonna fall down dead in the street from
exhaustion.
Speaking of which, I've not heard news\nregarding the aid Chelle was supposed\nto secure from Alberia.
Yes, and I fear we shouldn't get our hopes\nup on that front.
It seems dragons infested with black mana\nhave begun to crop up in Alberia.
Sadly, my dear brother Leonidas has his\nhands quite full dealing with that situation.
I doubt he'll be able to lend any people\nto our cause at present.
Such timing is ill news indeedâ€”though\nperhaps all of our problems are related.
That mirrors my own opinion, Elisanne.\nThis cannot be mere coincidence.
There's likely someone out there who\nwishes to prevent anyone from interfering\nwith Grams.
Come to think of it, Nedrick said somethin'\nabout how black mana is the power of the\nProgenitor.
And our foes include someone who\ncan use black mana. It's clear who's\nresponsible here.
I can scarcely fathom the idea of warring\nagainst the very creator of the world...
Makes me miss the days I spent tusslin'\nwith bandits and whatnot. All this heady\ncrap is too much for ol' Ranzal.
But if we don't fight, the very concept\nof possibility will disappear forever!
Oh, don't get me wrongâ€”I'm gonna fight\nthe chump to my last breath whether he's\nthe creator of the world or not.
That said, we are at a bit of a stalemate\nuntil we find a way to clear this miasma.
Yes, it seems we'll just have to ask about\nthat directly.
Yes. As we can tell from their efforts to\nprevent aid from coming here, our enemy's\ntarget must be Grams.

In fact, I imagine my miserable brothers
are somewhere in this city as we speakâ€”
no doubt gloating amongst themselves
all the while...
